<br>
I don't think there is any tradeskills out there that can get you to 250 from vendor items. And if there was, I would think it would be alot of $$.<br>
If you want to do any tradeskill you have to expect to farm items..unless you have a ton of pp and willing to buy the mob drop items in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
All tradeskills at one point or another require the skill of another tradeskill/character class.<br>
<br>
Diety plays zero part in pottery if you are just looking to get skill rises..If you were smithing it would be a different case.<br>
<br>
As a person that is trying to raise pottery, never expect a skill rise, because when you get one you will be on a high all day.<br>
Pottery, back in May of last year (I think) was one of the tradeskills that was made harder to gain skill rises.<br>
<br>
Most of all, take the time to do some research on the tradeskill. Look at recipes, what they require, what they cost to make etc.. but most of all put Eqtraders on your favorites list.<br>
<br>
<br>
